Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Temporin 1Vb (Temporin-1Vb, XXA, natural AMPs; UCLL1c; frog, amphibians, animals)
Sequence Information.Source: skin, Carpenter Frog,Rana virgatipes(Ranidae, Aquarana), USA, North America

Literature Information.Literature: C-terminal NH2.Activity: Active against S. aureus NCTC8325 (MIC 5 uM), MRSA T7/20 (MIC 10 uM),  S. epidermidis RP62A (MIC 5 uM), E. faecalis ATCC 29212 (MIC 20 uM), Streptococcus group B HNTCC 80130 (MIC 20 uM), E.coli ATCC25922 (MIC >160 uM), K.pneumoniae KK3 9904 (MIC >160 uM), P.aeruginosa ATCC 27853 (MIC >160 uM), E. cloacae HNTCC 53001(MIC >160 uM), and C.albicans (MIC >160 uM).Toxicity: moderate hemllytic HC50 30 uM. Updated 5/2020; 7/2021
Literature Information.Author: Conlon JM et al Bevier CR2005
Literature Information.Title: Purification and characterization of antimicrobial peptides from the skin secretions of the carpenter frog Rana virgatipes (Ranidae, Aquarana).
